===Related terms===

Inside-Outside: A paradoxic phrase usually denominating the relationship between the two antonyms. Successfully used as a company name for any business related to outdoor events, such as Inside Outside who operate a <a href="[http://www.inside-outside.co.uk/]">marquee hire</a> service which provides an inside [of a marquee, a covering] outside [in the garden, field or lawn].